<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-6 sm:py-8" style="view-transition-name: page-content;">
  <%= render "shared/navbar", title: "SETTINGS", current: "settings" %>

  <!-- FAQ Card -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm mb-6">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-base-content/50">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="join join-vertical w-full mt-2">
        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" checked="checked" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">What video formats are supported?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            MP4, QuickTime (.mov), WebM, AVI, and MPEG formats are supported. Maximum file size is 200MB.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">How does the video analysis work?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            Videos are uploaded to Google's Gemini AI which analyzes them for scene descriptions, speech transcription, and sound effects. The AI generates timestamp-segmented annotations and a newsreader script.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">What is Cloudflare Stream?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            Cloudflare Stream provides video hosting and delivery. Videos are uploaded directly to Cloudflare, encoded for streaming, and can be embedded using their player.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">How long are sessions kept?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            After analyzing a video, the session is kept for 30 minutes. During this time you can ask follow-up questions about the video. After 30 minutes the session and Gemini file are automatically deleted.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">What voices are available for text-to-speech?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            30 voices are available through Google's Gemini TTS model. The default voice is Kore. You can select different voices from the dropdown after generating a newsreader script.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
